## Database Tables
- `llmConversations`: id, id_users, id_sections, id_llm_scripts, title, model, temperature, max_tokens, blocked, deleted
- `llmMessages`: id, id_llmConversations, role (user/assistant/system), content, attachments, model, tokens_used, raw_response, sent_context, reasoning, id_dataRows, is_validated, request_payload, deleted
- `llmConversationProgress`: id, id_llmConversations, id_sections, progress_percentage, topic_coverage
- `llm_scripts`: id, generated_id, name, script, data_config, test_variables, async, model, temperature, max_tokens

## Registered Styles
- **llmChat**: Full chat interface (React-powered), style group "Form"
- **llmResponse**: Display LLM response data with `{{field.path}}` interpolation
- **llmFormRecord** (v1.1.0): LLM-enhanced form in record mode (extends formUserInputRecord + LLM generation)
- **llmFormLog** (v1.1.0): LLM-enhanced form in log mode (extends formUserInputLog + LLM generation)

## Key Service Classes
| Service | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| LlmService | Core: conversations CRUD, messages CRUD, `callLlmApi()` (synchronous POST, no SSE) |
| LlmContextService | Builds API messages array from conversation history + system context |
| LlmResponseService | `callLlmWithSchemaValidation()` — calls LLM + validates JSON schema + retries |
| LlmDataSavingService | Saves form data to `dataTables` via `UserInput::save_data()` |
| LlmFormModeService | Handles form mode metadata |
| LlmDangerDetectionService | Safety keyword detection + blocking |

## LLM API Call Flow
1. Controller receives POST request
2. `LlmContextService::buildApiMessages()` builds message array with context
3. `LlmResponseService::callLlmWithSchemaValidation()` calls LLM
4. Inside: `LlmService::callLlmApi()` — synchronous HTTP POST to provider (stream: false)
5. Response validated against JSON schema, retries up to 3x on failure
6. Result saved to `llmMessages` table
7. JSON response returned to React frontend

## React Architecture
- Entry: `LLMChat.tsx` finds `.llm-chat-root` elements, parses `data-config` JSON, renders `<LlmChatLoader>`
- Config loaded via API (`?action=get_config`) with data-attribute fallback
- Key shared components: `MarkdownRenderer`, `MessageList`, `FormRenderer`, `LoadingIndicator`
- All markdown rendered via `react-markdown` + `remark-gfm` + `rehype-highlight` + `rehype-raw`

## Hook Registrations
- `field-llm-model-edit/view`: Custom CMS field for LLM model dropdown
- `field-floating-button-position-edit/view`: Position dropdown
- `field-audio-model-edit/view`: Audio model dropdown
- `field-llm_panel-edit/view`: Admin panel widget
- `llm-execute-llm-task`: Execute LLM script tasks
- `llm-jobConfig-schema`, `llm-get-task-config`, `llm-get-job-type`: Job scheduler integration

## Constants (globals.php)
`LLM_DEFAULT_MODEL`, `LLM_DEFAULT_TEMPERATURE` (1), `LLM_DEFAULT_MAX_TOKENS` (2048), `LLM_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` (30), `TRANSACTION_BY_LLM_PLUGIN`, `LLM_VISION_MODELS`, `LLM_AUDIO_MODELS`

## Template Pattern
PHP view includes template: `include __DIR__ . '/tpl/template.php'`
Template outputs `<div class="..." data-config="<?php echo htmlspecialchars($this->getReactConfig()); ?>">`
React mounts on the div, reads config from `data-config` attribute.

## Build System
Vite builds three separate UMD bundles: `llm-chat.umd.js`, `llm-admin.umd.js`, `llm-scripts.umd.js`
Gulp wrapper in `gulp/` handles npm install + Vite build.
